To understand this, you must scope Kemco games and other RPG's mindset... They have cool characters, exploration of dungeons and a store to tend. Just THIS proves to be a sustainable way of life... There is no point in ravaging through the world or abandon your father's workshop heritage, everything you need is right here in front of you... It is necessary entrepreneurship to survive here. With the right mindset, possibilities are endless... A real wild portable brainstorm for offline times.

Accidentally bought this game. However, it's actually incredibly good. Good systems for crafting, monster are interesting. Class system is excellent. Story is compelling and the shop mechanic for making money is simple to use. Excellent game.
Amazing game. 20 hours in, no money spent, and some of the best mobile gaming experience I've had. No bugs, no ads, just good rpg experience adjusted for mobile controls and time management.

Another staggeringly weak Kemco title. I feel like they've lost their touch. The crafting thing is great in this one, but the grind for resources is painful unless you spend money to buy the cash shop items. It becomes painful mid-game regardless as the amount of materials needed is ridiculous.

The game is definitely a throw back to old school JRPG's like final fantasy but don't expect an open world experience. Your world is limited to a town "menu" and dungeons "instanced maps to explore". Most of the gameplay is making new gear and fighting monsters for new gear materials. Overall it's a decent amount of fun but definitely not a epic adventure of world saving proportions
Its a very unique game

Awesome Game. Great TBRPG with making money from crafting and selling in your own shop. Class based system is awesome as well. Reminds me of the old school Final Fantasy. I can keep on going so try it out.

Good but not perfect In-app purchases in a Singleplayer game does not sit well with me but it's easy to obtain the "premium currency" through normal gameplay. Your party members can be customized as much as you want but they aren't given any dialogue at all in the story unlike Adventure Bar Story and Marenian Tavern. Unlocking recipes by mastering recipes is definitely better than Marenian Story's way unlocking by buying the recipe with gems outright (There are a lot of recipes). It's worth.

Really good game. The plot isn't all good but not bad either. The dialogue of the NPCs are funny and not bland so that's good. I like how there are many classes to choose from.

I played a lot of games before but never had I the chance to enjoy a game so much I played non-stop and finished it in 60hrs. With bare enough sleep. LOL. If you guys love strategic games, multi-class with SUBCLASS this is the game to enjoy. You can also play it offline, no internet network needed. As a blacksmith you get to enjoy grind and smith stuffs with lots of weapons and armors to choose from. They even provided variety of "cards" to boost gears attributes. I hope there's a 2nd part.

I LOVED Adventure Bar Story 2 and Marienian Tavern, and this is an improvement on those 2 games. You are a dungeon delving blacksmith shop owner. On a daily cycle you delve, craft, equip, open shop to sell. This game is meant to be grindy, but Auto Battle controls are helpful. Save file was 45 hours for lvl 99 with the minimal post game completed. 5/5, but not much replayability.

Super Fun JRPG. It was worth my money buying and i still haven't gone through it yet. The grinding mechanics as well as the subclass make it never a bore as you just keep on making new equipment and upgrading new skills to fight bigger and badder foes. Plus you can get diamonds(which usually you have to buy using money) passively by defeating enemys. The game is a turn base style rpg but with a set pattern(which have their on pros and cons). Overall good game a funny review option. 5/5

Game is programmed smooth as silk. A huge design upgrade to Marenian Tavern Story, and you're a blacksmith. Extra cool because you custom create a party of 5 adventurers, from a selection of traditional rpg classes. Select from a variety of religions to add bonuses to each character class. Later on each character can also take a sub class. After a half hour of playing the trial version, I had to get this game. If you like monster battling, collecting materials and crafting, this is your game.
